01/10/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Interior Minister Georgi Petkanov and his German counterpart, Otto Schilly, signed an agreement Tuesday (30 September) to co-operate in the fight against organised crime.
Schilly met also with National Assembly Chairman Ognyan Gerdzhikov and praised Bulgaria's progress towards EU integration.
In other news, a delegation from Bulgaria is in Brussels this week ahead of the European Commission's regular accession report, due in November.
The officials met with EU Enlargement Commissioner Guenter Verheugen, who praised Bulgaria's progress.
(Trud, 24 Chassa, Sega - 01/10/03;
BTA, BNT, BGNES, bTV, Nova TV - 30/09/03)
